<figureCitation box="[673,713,745,769]" captionStart-0="Figure 2" captionStart-1="Figure 3" captionStart-2="Figure 4" captionStartId-0="4.[143,210,1674,1696]" captionStartId-1="5.[211,278,1728,1750]" captionStartId-2="6.[143,210,1728,1750]" captionTargetBox-0="[162,1083,161,1640]" captionTargetBox-1="[225,1159,163,1694]" captionTargetBox-2="[198,1050,161,1694]" captionTargetId-0="figure-5@4.[162,1084,161,1641]" captionTargetId-1="figure-5@5.[225,1159,162,1695]" captionTargetId-2="figure-5@6.[198,1050,161,1694]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionTargetPageId-2="6" captionText-0="Figure 2. Pogonognathellus heterochros sp. nov. (A) Labrum; (B) mandible; (C) maxillary head (1–6: lamella 1–6); (D) maxillary outer lobe; (E) hypostomal setae in labial pulp; (F) dorsal cephalic macrochaetotaxy." captionText-1="Figure 3. Pogonognathellus heterochros sp. nov. (A) Dorsal tergal macrochaetotaxy; (B) trochanteral organ; (C) spiny inner setae on hind tibiotarsus." captionText-2="Figure 4. Pogonognathellus heterochros sp. nov. (A) Claw; (B) tenaculum; (C) dental spines; (D) mucro." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631143" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631145" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631149" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4631143/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4631145/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/4631149/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244">2–4</figureCitation>
