<paragraph blockId="2.[143,455,845,908]" box="[143,270,845,868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244">
<heading box="[143,270,845,868]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[143,270,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[143,455,845,908]" box="[143,455,883,908]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244">
<emphasis box="[143,283,884,908]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244">Body length.</emphasis>
Up to 
<quantity box="[363,452,883,907]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244" unit="mm" value="6.9">6.9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[143,1104,953,1105]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244">
<emphasis box="[143,282,954,978]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244">Body colour.</emphasis>
Scales brown. Ground colour white. Ant. III, head, Th. II, base of front and mid legs dark purple. Pigment on Ant. III darker at the base and gradually lighter towards tip. Eye patches black. Unpigmented spots on Th. II forming an irregular but relatively stable pattern. Anterior part of Th. III and femora of hind legs with diffuse purple pigment (
<figureCitation box="[329,448,1081,1105]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[143,210,1606,1628]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,1267,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-240@2.[145,1102,1267,1574]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. Body size and colour pattern of specimens in alcohol. (A) Pogonognathellus heterochros sp. nov.; (B) Pogonognathellus mai sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631137" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631137/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244">Figure 1A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[143,1103,1151,1207]" lastBlockId="3.[211,1172,167,510]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1245" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244">
<emphasis box="[143,211,1151,1175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1244">Head.</emphasis>
Antennae about 0.75 times body length, antennal length ratio as I: II: III + IV = 1.0: 1.4: 7.1–10.0, Ant. I, II and base of Ant. III scaled. Ommatidia 6 + 6. Labral setae four 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[406,418,168,192]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1245">/</emphasis>
five, five, four, all smooth, four setae of the third row thicker than others, labral margin with four spiny papillae, medial two curved and thinner, lateral two straight and stronger (
<figureCitation box="[512,632,231,255]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[143,210,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[162,1083,161,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-5@4.[162,1084,161,1641]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Pogonognathellus heterochros sp. nov. (A) Labrum; (B) mandible; (C) maxillary head (1–6: lamella 1–6); (D) maxillary outer lobe; (E) hypostomal setae in labial pulp; (F) dorsal cephalic macrochaetotaxy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631143/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1245">Figure 2A</figureCitation>
). Left and right mandible respectively with four and five apical teeth, a strong tapered tooth present distally on left molar plate and a hollow present in place on opposite side (
<figureCitation box="[689,808,295,319]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[143,210,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[162,1083,161,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-5@4.[162,1084,161,1641]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Pogonognathellus heterochros sp. nov. (A) Labrum; (B) mandible; (C) maxillary head (1–6: lamella 1–6); (D) maxillary outer lobe; (E) hypostomal setae in labial pulp; (F) dorsal cephalic macrochaetotaxy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631143/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1245">Figure 2B</figureCitation>
). Maxillary lamella 5 with long basal teeth, no distinct beard-like appendix observed (
<figureCitation box="[814,932,327,351]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[143,210,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[162,1083,161,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-5@4.[162,1084,161,1641]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Pogonognathellus heterochros sp. nov. (A) Labrum; (B) mandible; (C) maxillary head (1–6: lamella 1–6); (D) maxillary outer lobe; (E) hypostomal setae in labial pulp; (F) dorsal cephalic macrochaetotaxy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631143/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1245">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
). Papilla of maxillary outer lobe with four setae, one basal, one apical and two median, the apical one much stronger; sublobal plate with four guard setae (
<figureCitation box="[731,851,390,414]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[143,210,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[162,1083,161,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-5@4.[162,1084,161,1641]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Pogonognathellus heterochros sp. nov. (A) Labrum; (B) mandible; (C) maxillary head (1–6: lamella 1–6); (D) maxillary outer lobe; (E) hypostomal setae in labial pulp; (F) dorsal cephalic macrochaetotaxy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631143/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1245">Figure 2D</figureCitation>
). Labial palp A–E (
<bibRefCitation author="Fjellberg A" pageId="3" pageNumber="1245" pagination="309 - 330" refId="ref3688" refString="Fjellberg A. 1998. The labial palp in Collembola. Zoologischer Anzeiger 237: 309 - 330." type="journal article" year="1998">Fjellberg 1998</bibRefCitation>
) with zero, five, zero, four, seven guard setae, hypostomal setae H rod-like, h 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1161,1170,432,449]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="1245">1</subScript>
thicker and longer than h 
<subScript attach="left" box="[495,504,464,481]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="1245">2</subScript>
(
<figureCitation box="[520,637,454,478]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[143,210,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[162,1083,161,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-5@4.[162,1084,161,1641]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Pogonognathellus heterochros sp. nov. (A) Labrum; (B) mandible; (C) maxillary head (1–6: lamella 1–6); (D) maxillary outer lobe; (E) hypostomal setae in labial pulp; (F) dorsal cephalic macrochaetotaxy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631143/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1245">Figure 2E</figureCitation>
). Proximal, basomedian and basolateral area of labium each with about 40 setae.
</paragraph>
