<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="1249" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[211,1172,168,263]" box="[211,331,168,192]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249">
<heading box="[211,331,168,192]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[211,331,168,192]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[211,1172,168,263]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249">
Named for its unique cuticular colour. Greek word 
<emphasis box="[831,899,207,231]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249">hetero</emphasis>
for different, 
<emphasis box="[1069,1126,207,231]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249">chros</emphasis>
for pigmentation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="1249" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[211,1172,334,525]" box="[211,309,334,358]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249">
<heading box="[211,309,334,358]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[211,309,334,358]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[211,1172,334,525]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249">
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Yu &amp; Zhang, 2013" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yu &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2013" box="[211,541,374,398]" class="Collembola" family="Tomoceridae" genus="Pogonognathellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heterochros" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[211,541,374,398]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249">Pogonognathellus heterochros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[554,643,375,398]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maxillary" baseAuthorityName="Tullberg" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[808,949,374,398]" class="Collembola" family="Tomoceridae" genus="Pogonognathellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis box="[808,949,374,398]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249">P. flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in details, such as unguis, dental spines and mucro, but it lacks the long beard-like appendix at the base of maxillary lamella 5, which is a significant character in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maxillary" baseAuthorityName="Tullberg" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[886,1026,438,462]" class="Collembola" family="Tomoceridae" genus="Pogonognathellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis box="[886,1026,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249">P. flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yosii R" box="[1043,1167,438,462]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref3972" refString="Yosii R. 1967. Studies on the Collembolan family Tomoceridae, with special reference to Japanese forms. Contr Biol Lab Kyoto Univ. 20: 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="1967">Yosii 1967</bibRefCitation>
; Fjellberg; 2007; 
<bibRefCitation author="Felderhoff KL &amp; Bernard EC &amp; Moulton JK" box="[396,645,469,493]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1249" pagination="472 - 491" refId="ref3643" refString="Felderhoff KL, Bernard EC, Moulton JK. 2010. Survey of Pogonognathellus Borner (Collembola: Tomoceridae) in the Southern Appalachians based on morphological and molecular data. Ann Entomol Soc Am. 103 (4): 472 - 491." type="journal article" year="2010">Felderhoff et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). This new species can be easily recognized by the unique body colour in alcohol.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
